  <title>Gio.ActionMap</title>
  <synopsis><code>
const Gio = imports.gi.Gio;

let action_map = new Gio.ActionMap();
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>The GActionMap interface is implemented by <link xref="Gio.ActionGroup"/>
implementations that operate by containing a number of
named <link xref="Gio.Action"/> instances, such as <link xref="Gio.SimpleActionGroup"/>.</p>  <p>One useful application of this interface is to map the
names of actions from various action groups to unique,
prefixed names (e.g. by prepending "app." or "win.").
This is the motivation for the 'Map' part of the interface
name.</p>

  <synopsis>
    <title>Prerequisites</title>
    <p>ActionMap requires GObject.Object</p>
  </synopsis>
  <synopsis>
    <title>Known Implementations</title>
    <p>%s is implemented by Application and SimpleActionGroup</p>
  </synopsis>
